%N A394603 Decimal expansion of the aspect ratio of a rectangle with the property that the mean distance between two points selected independently at random within its interior is equal to the length of its smaller side.
%C A394603 The unique positive zero of 30*x^2 + 2*sqrt(1 + x^2)*(1 - 3*x^2 + x^4) - 2*(1 + x^5) - 5*x*(arcsinh(x) + x^3*arcsinh(1/x)).
%H A394603 Birendranath Ghosh, <a href="https://archive.org/details/dli.calcutta.11610/page/17/mode/1up">Random distances within a rectangle and between two rectangles</a>, Bulletin of Calcutta Mathematical Society, Vol. 43 (1951), pp. 17-24.
%e A394603 2.641871923175326849790036252460124287136265551024037...
%t A394603 RealDigits[x /. FindRoot[30*x^2 + 2*Sqrt[1 + x^2]*(1 - 3*x^2 + x^4) - 2*(1 + x^5) - 5*x*(ArcSinh[x] + x^3*ArcSinh[1/x]), {x, 2}, WorkingPrecision -> 120]][[1]]
%o A394603 (PARI) solve(x = 2, 3, 30*x^2 + 2*sqrt(1 + x^2)*(1 - 3*x^2 + x^4) - 2*(1 + x^5) - 5*x*(asinh(x) + x^3*asinh(1/x)))
